&lt;h1&gt;South Tees Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Neurorehabilitation &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an experienced Consultant in Neurorehabilitation to join the team at The James Cook University Hospital. This is a new appointment to join two existing colleagues (one FT and one PT) in a level 2B neurorehabilitation unit integrated within a major trauma centre, with full supporting facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neurorehabilitation service serves a population of approximately 1.3 million in Teesside, North Yorkshire and County Durham. The service has its own dedicated ward for “post-acute” inpatient rehabilitation where it provides comprehensive physiotherapy, occupational therapy, speech and language therapy and Neuropsychology support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At The James Cook University Hospital comprehensive facilities, all on one site include: 20 bed ITU, PICU, 4 clean air theatres, specialist radiology support, with 24/7 MRI and other imaging, Major Trauma Centre, and neurophysiology, cardio-thoracic, plastic and specialist paediatric support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research is actively encouraged and there are research links with the Universities of Durham, Newcastle and Teesside. The centre is currently taking part in a stage two trial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is progressive, and we are looking for an energetic and enthusiastic colleague to help shape future direction. The facilities can accommodate any special interest and this will be encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should possess full GMC registration, MRCP/ MRCS or equivalent and completed a CCT in rehabilitation medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full consideration will be given to applicants who wish to apply for a part time contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Tees Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest Trusts in England, comprising of The James Cook University Hospital, Middlesbrough and the Friarage Hospital, Northallerton. The James Cook University Hospital is a major tertiary and teaching centre with over 1,000 beds, serving a largely urban population It provides comprehensive regional specialties including Cardiothoracic Surgery, Neurosurgery, Maxillofacial Surgery, Plastic Surgery, ENT and Ophthalmic Surgery. It is a regional centre for Spinal Cord Injury, Upper GI and Vascular Surgery. All other major specialties are catered for. The Friarage Hospital, Northallerton, serves a population of 120,000 covering 1,000 sq miles of rural North Yorkshire, and provides local medical services for the area. The hospital has recently undergone major re-development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The quality of life for professionals and their families in the North East of England is good with easy access to attractive countryside and beaches, a choice of highly rated schools and good travel access to the North and Scotland, the Lake District or the South by road, rail or air.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Description and further details available from NHS Jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should be made online via NHS Jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
